-- Ford's June U.S. Vehicle Sales Climb 13%, Missing Analysts' 16% Estimate
-- Bill Koenig
-- 2010-07-01T16:04:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/ford-s-june-u-s-vehicle-sales-climb-13-missing-analysts-16-estimate.html

          
          
             Ford Motor Co. said its June U.S.
vehicle sales rose 13 percent.  
 The average estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was
an increase of 16 percent.  
 Ford said sales of its F-Series pickup trucks rose 30
percent to 46,502 units while sales of its Fusion car fell 0.8
percent to 18,412 units.  
          
          


  


        